    <string name="about_app_summary">Tryst is a private, local-only journal for your intimate life. Log encounters in as much detail as you like — partners, acts, positions, protection, mood, place, occasion, toys, kinks, a rating, orgasms, notes, and encrypted photos — then explore on-device Insights and Achievements built entirely from your own history.\n\nEvery category is yours. Tryst ships almost nothing predefined: it starts you off with a few neutral entries (like Kissing or Date night) that are just editable rows, and you add, rename, or remove your own acts, kinks, positions, toys, occasions, and finish locations under Settings → Categories. Everything you add counts fully across Insights and Achievements.\n\nNothing ever leaves your phone — no account, no sync, no internet access at all.</string>
    <string name="about_license_body">Tryst is free, open-source software, licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3). You may use, study, share, and modify it; redistributed versions must also be GPLv3 and ship their source. The full license text is in the LICENSE file of the source repository.</string>
